  "prompt": "What are some mind blowing iphone cases that most people don't know about?",
  "response": "There are some truly unique and innovative iPhone cases out there that many people might not be aware of. Here are a few examples:\n\n1. **Moscase**: This customizable modular phone case monitors vital signs and includes swappable modules, such as a breathalyzer, solar charger, and speakers.\n\n2. **Flask iPhone Case**: Designed for those who enjoy a cheeky drink, this case has a built-in flask to discreetly carry your favorite beverage.\n\n3. **Prynt Case**: This case turns your iPhone into a mini instant printer, allowing you to print photos on the spot directly from your phone.\n\n4. **Circle**: An iPhone case with an integrated retractable charging cable. It's incredibly convenient for those who often forget their charging cables.\n\n5. **Lunatik Epik**: This robust case not only protects your iPhone but also transforms it into an Apple Watch. Yes, a case that integrates your watch for an all-in-one device.\n\n6. **Game Boy Case**: A nostalgic case featuring a working replica of the original Game Boy complete with pre-installed games.\n\n7. **Handwarmer Case**: Perfect for winter months, this case not only protects your iPhone but also keeps your hands warm with built-in hand warmers.\n\n8. **Eyejust Anti-Blue Light Screen Protector Case**: A case equipped with a screen protector that blocks harmful blue light emissions from your iPhone\u2019s display.\n\n9. **Sandwich iPhone Case**: A whimsical case that mimics the look of a sandwich or burger, adding fun and humor to your everyday carry.\n\n10. **SmartBoy Case**: Designed for gamers, this case turns your iPhone into a fully functional gaming device complete with physical buttons for an authentic handheld gaming experience.\n\nThese cases range from functional to whimsical, showcasing the creativity and innovation in the accessory market for iPhone users.",
